steps.description:
src/server/handlers.ts:166-200 — the two helpers `readJsonBody` and `readJsonBodyOrEmpty` are near-identical: same JSON.parse + same try/catch + same `request body must be JSON: ...` message + same `request body must be a JSON object` non-object guard. The only real difference is the empty-body branch: `readJsonBody` throws `request body is empty; expected a JSON object`; `readJsonBodyOrEmpty` returns null.

Refactor `readJsonBody` to delegate:

  async function readJsonBody(ctx: RouteContext): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {
    const parsed = await readJsonBodyOrEmpty(ctx);
    if (parsed === null) {
      throw new ValidationError("request body is empty; expected a JSON object");
    }
    return parsed;
  }

Keep every emitted error string byte-identical to today's so handler tests that match on error.message still pass. Verify by reading the few tests that assert on these specific strings (grep `request body is empty`, `request body must be JSON`, `request body must be a JSON object` under src/server). No signature changes. No new exports. Pure structural dedup; the diff should net out to a removal of ~14 lines. Run `bun run check:all` before opening the PR.
